One day I want to speak to a group of teenagers about how writing a blog and having self confidence can help them succeed in life. How having a job at a company will allow them to use these skills in different ways. How debate, negotiation and communication skills are invaluable no matter where you work. 

Goal accomplished! I had the pleasure of speaking to my son’s high school Model UN competition a couple of weeks ago. He said he nominated me because I’m a celebrity. I quietly cried happy tears after he told me that because he’s such an amazing kid. 

I do this for them. It’s what keeps me going. I don’t do it for money or fame (yes those are nice too!) but I do it so people see others that look like them and encourage them to go do the damn thing. 

Forever grateful for this speaking opportunity and forever grateful for the life I live. ❤️❤️

I got to try @eat.birdcall and I think it’s going to be one of my new fave chicken places! 

It’s new new to the area and I was impressed with the quality of food and drinks. You order at the counter yourself and pick up your own food as well. They have a large variety of drinks and shakes and you can even treat yourself to margaritas or other alcoholic drinks. 

Here’s what we tried: 

Original Chicken Sandwich 
Buffalo Chicken Sandwich 
Chop Salad 
5 Piece Tenders
Fries
Tater Tots (my fave)
Tractor Punch
Peanut Butter Chocolate Shake 

I will definitely go back another time- the salads are great for lunch too!
